  === section: port subcommands ===
  Subcommands of /port:
    /port.baud_rate {value} - Show or set baud rate.
    /port.break {duration_ms} - Send a break signal (default 250ms).
    /port.byte_size {value} - Show or set data bits.
    /port.cd - Show Carrier Detect state (read-only).
    /port.close - Disconnect from the serial port.
    /port.cts - Show CTS state (read-only).
    /port.dsr - Show DSR state (read-only).
    /port.dtr {0|1} - Show or set DTR line (hardware only).
    /port.flow_control {mode} - Show or set flow control (none/rtscts/xonxoff/manual).
    /port.info - Show port status, serial parameters, and hardware lines.
    /port.list - List available serial ports.
    /port.open {name} - Connect to the serial port (optional port override).
    /port.parity {value} - Show or set parity.
    /port.ri - Show Ring Indicator state (read-only).
    /port.rts {0|1} - Show or set RTS line (hardware only).
    /port.stop_bits {value} - Show or set stop bits.
